This paper discusses methodologies for network management and anomaly detection, which are primarily related to computer networks (cs.NI). It also mentions the use of data analysis pipelines, which falls under the category of data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of custom agents and large data centralization systems, which are related to security (cs.CR) and system architecture (cs.SE), respectively. Finally, the paper mentions the deployment of these methodologies in real industrial production environments, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
